exercise.p:

	\begin{aligned}
		238 \amp = 200 + 30 + 8 \\
		\amp = 2 \cdot 100 + 3 \cdot 10 + 8 \cdot 1 \\
		\amp = 2 \cdot 10^2 + 3 \cdot 10^1 + 8 \cdot 10^0 
	\end{aligned}

With this framework in mind, write the number 21.84 using expanded form and showing the powers of ten.

